  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Export Control Manager",
  "description": "<p>Our esteemed client is seeking an <strong>Assistant Export Control Manager</strong> to support and strengthen governance across defence and strategic goods exports. This role sits at the intersection of compliance, regulation, and stakeholder advisory within a highly regulated environment.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage import/export policies and procedures in compliance with the Singapore Customs Act and U.S. Export Control Regulations</li><li>Advise internal stakeholders and respond to end-user queries on export control and trade compliance matters</li><li>Monitor and interpret local and international trade regulations, including customs, export controls, and trade restrictions</li><li>Establish and maintain best practices for export-controlled items, including documentation across the asset lifecycle</li><li>Prepare compliance documentation and maintain audit-ready records for internal reviews and regulatory inspections</li><li>Support and coordinate export compliance training and awareness initiatives</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in export control, trade compliance, or governance roles</li><li>Strong knowledge of the Singapore Strategic Goods (Control) Act</li><li>Familiarity with U.S. Export Control Regulations (ITAR, EAR) is an advantage</li><li>Exposure to defence, military, or highly regulated technology industries preferred</li></ul><p><strong>To Apply</strong><br />To apply or find out more information on this role, please email us or send in your updated resume to:<br /><a href=\"#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">lynn.tay@starcareerconsulting.com</a></p><p><strong>Lynn Tay</strong> (Reg. No. R1876711)<br /><strong>STAR CAREER CONSULTING PTE LTD</strong> (EA Licence: 20C0353)</p>",
